The paper deals with resource-aware algorithms for distributed inter-robot loop closure detection, which is a problem commonly encountered in robotics and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes a framework for selecting a subset of potential inter-robot loop closures for geometric verification, which involves optimization and approximation algorithms. This suggests that the paper could also belong to categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
